Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.59,0:00:03.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,This episode of Real Engineering is brought to you by Brilliant,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.84,0:00:07.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,a problem solving website that teaches you to think like an engineer.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.69,0:00:13.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,2019年5月24日 太空叉的猎鹰九号火箭一次发射了60颗卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.69,0:00:13.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,On the 24th of May, SpaceX launched a Falcon 9 rocket filled with 60 satellites into space.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:14.11,0:00:17.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,迈出了他们宏伟的Starlink计划的第一步
Dialogue: 2,0:00:14.11,0:00:17.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,This marked the beginning of their ambitious new project called “Starlink”
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.96,0:00:23.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,该计划致力于为全球偏远地区提供高通量的互联网服务
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.96,0:00:23.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,which aims to provide high quality broadband internet to the most isolated parts of the planet,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:23.70,0:00:28.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,以及为已有覆盖地区提供更低延迟的通信服务
Dialogue: 2,0:00:23.70,0:00:28.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,while also providing low latency connectivity to already well connected cities.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.88,0:00:32.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉的目标是让大家都能用上
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.88,0:00:32.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX aim to make their broadband as accessible as possible,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:32.58,0:00:38.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们说只要买了其自主研发的披萨盒大小的天线 任何人就都能上网
Dialogue: 2,0:00:32.58,0:00:38.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,claiming that anyone will be able to connect to their network if they buy the pizza box-sized antenna
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.21,0:00:40.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们说只要买了其自主研发的披萨盒大小的天线 任何人就都能上网
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.21,0:00:40.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,which SpaceX is developing themselves.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:40.78,0:00:44.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这次发射的60颗卫星 只是其中第一批
Dialogue: 2,0:00:40.78,0:00:44.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,This launch of 60 satellites, was just the first of many.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.42,0:00:49.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉在未来十年计划发射12000颗卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.42,0:00:49.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,Spacex has 12,000 satellites planned for launch over the next decade,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:49.49,0:00:54.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,这会极大增加地球在轨卫星的总数量
Dialogue: 2,0:00:49.49,0:00:54.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,dramatically increasing the total amount of spacecraft around Earth's orbit.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:54.22,0:00:59.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,这一举动会花掉太空叉数十亿美元 所以希望他们能回本
Dialogue: 2,0:00:54.22,0:00:59.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,This will cost SpaceX billions of dollars, so they must have a good reason for doing so.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:59.44,0:01:05.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们今天来了解一下这个网络是如何工作的 以及它将如何击败现有网络服务商
Dialogue: 2,0:00:59.44,0:01:05.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let's see how this network will work, and how it will compete with existing internet providers.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:05.55,0:01:11.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,回到2015年 马一龙宣布太空叉开始研发一款卫星通信网络
Dialogue: 2,0:01:05.55,0:01:11.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,Back in 2015, Elon announced that SpaceX had began working on a communication satellite network,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:11.93,0:01:17.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,他说目前全球范围的廉价宽频带卫星间通信有很大的市场需求
Dialogue: 2,0:01:11.93,0:01:17.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,stating that there is a significant unmet demand for low-cost global broadband capabilities.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:17.66,0:01:22.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,大约在那阵 太空叉在华盛顿州雷德蒙开了新工厂
Dialogue: 2,0:01:17.66,0:01:22.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Around that time, SpaceX opened a new facility in Redmond, Washington
Dialogue: 1,0:01:22.04,0:01:25.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,专门研发制造这些新的通信卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:01:22.04,0:01:25.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,to develop and manufacture these new communication satellites.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.01,0:01:30.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,原本计划是在2016年发射两颗原型卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.01,0:01:30.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,The initial plan was to launch two prototype satellites into orbit by 2016
Dialogue: 1,0:01:30.80,0:01:35.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,然后让初始的卫星星座在2020年开始运营
Dialogue: 2,0:01:30.80,0:01:35.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,and have the initial satellite constellation up and running by 2020.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:35.12,0:01:41.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,但太空叉在研发老百姓都会装的廉价接收机上遇到了小麻烦
Dialogue: 2,0:01:35.12,0:01:41.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the company struggled to develop a receiver that could be easily installed by the user for a low cost,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:41.07,0:01:46.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,导致计划有所推迟 直到2018年 两颗原型卫星才发射
Dialogue: 2,0:01:41.07,0:01:46.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,this delayed the program and the initial prototype satellites weren't launched until 2018.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.75,0:01:50.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,在两颗原型卫星——丁丁A和丁丁B发射后
Dialogue: 2,0:01:46.75,0:01:50.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,After a successful launch of the two prototypes, Tintin-A and B,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.84,0:01:54.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉可以开始测试并修改他们的卫星设计
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.84,0:01:54.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,which allowed SpaceX to test and refine their satellite design,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:54.16,0:01:58.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,之后太空叉对Starlink计划公布的内容开始变少
Dialogue: 2,0:01:54.16,0:01:58.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX kept pretty quiet about what was next for the Starlink project,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.17,0:02:06.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,直到2018年11月 太空叉拿到了FCC颁发的 发射7500颗卫星入轨的许可
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.17,0:02:06.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,until November 2018 when SpaceX received the approval from the FCC to deploy 7,500 satellites into orbit,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:06.46,0:02:10.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,外加之前已经通过审批的4400颗卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:02:06.46,0:02:10.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,on top of the 4,400 that were already approved.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.40,0:02:15.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,在2019年5月24日 首批卫星发射入轨
Dialogue: 2,0:02:10.40,0:02:15.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,On May 24th, the first batch of production satellites were launched into orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:02:15.32,0:02:20.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,全世界的人们很快发现了划过夜空的这一串卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:02:15.32,0:02:20.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,and people around the world quickly started to spot the train of satellites moving across the night sky.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.06,0:02:23.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,这次发射预示着一个新的潮流要来了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:21.06,0:02:23.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,This launch is a sign of things to come,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.52,0:02:26.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然第一批卫星的功能并不完备
Dialogue: 2,0:02:23.52,0:02:26.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,while this initial group of satellites are not fully functional,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.66,0:02:30.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,它们主要用于测试地球通信系统
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.66,0:02:30.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,they will be used to test things like the earth communications systems
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.59,0:02:36.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,与用于躲避太空垃圾和在寿终正寝时用于离轨的氪推进器
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.59,0:02:36.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the krypton thrusters which will be used to autonomously avoid debris and de-orbit the spacecraft
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.03,0:02:38.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,与用于躲避太空垃圾和在寿终正寝时用于离轨的氪推进器
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.03,0:02:38.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,once it has reached the end of its lifecycle.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.66,0:02:41.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们先来看看这些功能
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.66,0:02:41.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let's look at these functionalities first.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:41.37,0:02:46.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们以前已经了解过离子推进器的工作原理 大家可以前去观看以了解更多细节
Dialogue: 2,0:02:41.37,0:02:46.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,We have explored how ion thrusters work in the past, which you can watch for more detail,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.34,0:02:52.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,简言之就是利用电势能将带电粒子发射出去 从而提供推力
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.34,0:02:52.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,but essentially they use electric potential to fire ions out of the spacecraft to provide propulsion.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:52.51,0:02:58.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,氙是比较理想的选择 因为它原子量够高 每个原子可以提供更多的动能
Dialogue: 2,0:02:52.51,0:02:58.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,Xenon is ideally used, because it has a high atomic mass allowing it to provide more kick per atom,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.73,0:03:04.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,其自身是惰性气体 存储密度高 可以在航天器上储存很久
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.73,0:03:04.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,while being inert and having a high storage density lending itself to long term storage on a spacecraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.06,0:03:11.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,但太空叉选择了氪 因为氙作为燃料太贵了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.06,0:03:11.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,However SpaceX opted for krypton, as xenon's rarity makes it a far more expensive propellant.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.34,0:03:15.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,卫星的离子推进器会首先用于给Starlink卫星升轨
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.34,0:03:15.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,This ion thruster will initially be used to raise the starlink satellites
Dialogue: 1,0:03:15.53,0:03:22.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,从星箭分离的440公里提高到最终运行的550公里
Dialogue: 2,0:03:15.53,0:03:22.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,from their release orbits at 440 km to their final orbital height of 550 km.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.56,0:03:28.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,它们还将和卫星上装有的陀螺仪配合
Dialogue: 2,0:03:22.56,0:03:28.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,They will also be used in conjunction with on board control momentum gyroscopes located here,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.53,0:03:32.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,并结合美国政府太空垃圾相撞预警系统
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.53,0:03:32.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the US Governments' space debris collision prediction system
Dialogue: 1,0:03:32.44,0:03:36.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,让卫星能够自行调整轨道避开太空垃圾
Dialogue: 2,0:03:32.44,0:03:36.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,to allow the satellites to adjust their orbits to dodge collisions,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:36.10,0:03:39.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,这在之前视频也有提到
Dialogue: 2,0:03:36.10,0:03:39.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,which we have also spoken about in more detail in a previous video.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.04,0:03:42.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,当卫星达到了寿命期限
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.04,0:03:42.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,When the satellites have reached the end of their service life
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.84,0:03:47.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,它们还能用同样的姿态控制器和推进器进行离轨
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.84,0:03:47.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,they can then use the same attitude controls and thrusters to de-orbit the satellite.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:47.87,0:03:52.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉为了防止卫星成为太空垃圾 使用了所有必要的设备
Dialogue: 2,0:03:47.87,0:03:52.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX have included all the necessary hardware to minimize space debris risk.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.12,0:03:56.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,在他们的FCC审批申请表中
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.12,0:03:56.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,In their Federal Communications Commission approval application,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:56.60,0:04:01.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们声称卫星95%的部分会在再入大气时烧毁
Dialogue: 2,0:03:56.60,0:04:01.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,they claim that 95% of the satellite will burn up on re-entry.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.23,0:04:07.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,只有离子推进器的内部结构和碳化硅组件能挺过再入的高温
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.23,0:04:07.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,With only the ion thruster internal structure and silicon carbide components, standing a chance of survival.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.64,0:04:10.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,只剩碳化硅零件的原因 一方面它是必需零件 一方面是它本身熔点高达2750°C
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.64,0:04:10.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,Those silicon carbide components are likely to survive,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.86,0:04:19.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,只剩碳化硅零件的原因 一方面它是必需零件 一方面是它本身熔点高达2750°C
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.86,0:04:19.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,as they are essential materials and thus have an extremely high melting point of 2,750°C.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:19.73,0:04:24.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,那么话题就到了卫星的主要功能——通信了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:19.73,0:04:24.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Which brings us to our communications abilities, the primary function of the satellite.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.70,0:04:28.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉对卫星的很多细节都讳莫如深
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.70,0:04:28.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX have been tight lipped on many of the details of the satellite,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.51,0:04:35.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,但多亏了FCC的文件 我们了解到卫星有五块1.5千克的碳化硅组件
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.51,0:04:35.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,but thanks to that FCC filing we know that the satellites will contain 5 1.5 kilogram silicon carbide components,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:35.97,0:04:40.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,这可能表示每颗卫星会有五个独立的激光发射器
Dialogue: 2,0:04:35.97,0:04:40.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,which indicates that each satellite will contain 5 individual lasers.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:40.61,0:04:43.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些激光 就像我们在地球上用的光纤一样
Dialogue: 2,0:04:40.61,0:04:43.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,These lasers, like our fibre optic cables here on earth,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:43.96,0:04:48.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,使用光脉冲在卫星之间传递信息
Dialogue: 2,0:04:43.96,0:04:48.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,will use light pulses to transmit information between satellites.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.65,0:04:52.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,相比于在地球 太空中的激光传输有很多优势
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.65,0:04:52.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,Transmitting with light in space offers one massive advantage
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.62,0:04:55.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,相比于在地球 太空中的激光传输有很多优势
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.62,0:04:55.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,over transmitting with light here on earth however.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:55.45,0:04:59.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,事实上 光速在不同介质中速度是不同的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:55.45,0:04:59.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,The speed of light is not constant in every material, in fact,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:59.78,0:05:04.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,光在玻璃中的速度比在真空中慢47%
Dialogue: 2,0:04:59.78,0:05:04.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,light travels 47% slower in glass than in a vacuum.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:04.73,0:05:10.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,这给Starlink一个极大的优势 很可能成为其首要卖点
Dialogue: 2,0:05:04.73,0:05:10.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,This offers Starlink one huge advantage that will likely be it's primary money maker.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:10.14,0:05:14.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,它可以提供长距离下的低时延通信
Dialogue: 2,0:05:10.14,0:05:14.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,It provides the potential of lower latency information over long distance,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.98,0:05:19.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,作为简化 我们想象以下数据传输的例子
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.98,0:05:19.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,in simpler terms let's imagine this as a race between data packets.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.20,0:05:26.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,一名伦敦的用户想要了解纽交所纳斯达克某股票的最新价格
Dialogue: 2,0:05:19.20,0:05:26.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,A user in London wants the new adjusted price of a stock on the NASDAQ from the New York stock exchange.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.21,0:05:31.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果该信息使用传统路线 比如AC-2光缆
Dialogue: 2,0:05:26.21,0:05:31.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,If this information were to use a typical route, let's say through the AC-2 cable,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:31.02,0:05:37.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,往返路程12800公里 介质是光导纤维
Dialogue: 2,0:05:31.02,0:05:37.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,which has a return journey of about 12,800 kilometres to make through our glass fibre optic cable.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:37.56,0:05:45.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,真空中的光速是299792458米每秒
Dialogue: 2,0:05:37.56,0:05:45.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,In a vacuum light travels at a speed of 299,792,458 meters per second.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:45.88,0:05:51.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,光纤中的光速取决于折射率 而折射率取决于波长
Dialogue: 2,0:05:45.88,0:05:51.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,The speed of travel in glass depends on the refractive index and the refractive index depends on wavelength,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:51.46,0:05:57.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们取真空中的光速比光纤中快1.47倍
Dialogue: 2,0:05:51.46,0:05:57.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,but we will take the reduction as 1.47 times slower than the speed of light in a vacuum.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:57.21,0:06:03.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,算下来 数据包来回要走0.063秒
Dialogue: 2,0:05:57.21,0:06:03.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,This means the data packet will take roughly 0.063 seconds to make the round trip,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:03.49,0:06:10.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,也就是有0.063秒的延迟 或62.7毫秒
Dialogue: 2,0:06:03.49,0:06:10.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,and thus has a latency of 0.063 seconds, or 62.7 milliseconds.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:10.36,0:06:13.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,外加一些额外的延迟
Dialogue: 2,0:06:10.36,0:06:13.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,With the additional steps that add to this latency
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.12,0:06:17.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,比如光缆两端的光电转换
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.12,0:06:17.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,like the conversion of light signals to electrical signals on either end of the optical cable,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:17.73,0:06:25.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,数据的队列 以及到终端电脑的时间 最终时延可以达到76毫秒
Dialogue: 2,0:06:17.73,0:06:25.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,traffic queues, and the transfer to our final computer terminal, this total time comes out at about 76 ms.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:25.63,0:06:31.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,计算出Starlink的延迟要困难得多 因为我们没有现实的例子
Dialogue: 2,0:06:25.63,0:06:31.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Figuring out the latency for Starlink is a lot more difficult, as we have no real world measurements to go by,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:31.85,0:06:35.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,但我们可以参考伦敦大学学院通信教授Mark Handley的猜测
Dialogue: 2,0:06:31.85,0:06:35.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,but we can make some educated guesses with the help of Mark Handley,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:35.44,0:06:38.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,但我们可以参考伦敦大学学院通信教授Mark Handley的猜测
Dialogue: 2,0:06:35.44,0:06:38.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,a communications professor in University College London.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:39.17,0:06:43.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,第一种延迟产生于上星与下星过程
Dialogue: 2,0:06:39.17,0:06:43.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,The first source of latency for Starlink will be during the up and down link process,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:43.84,0:06:47.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们要让信息从地球上行到卫星 再下行回地球
Dialogue: 2,0:06:43.84,0:06:47.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,where we need to transfer our information to and from earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:47.28,0:06:50.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,这可以通过相控阵列实现
Dialogue: 2,0:06:47.28,0:06:50.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,We know this will be done with phase array antenna,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:50.41,0:06:55.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,不需要移动天线位置 就能让天线组传输信号
Dialogue: 2,0:06:50.41,0:06:55.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,which are radio antenna that can control the direction of their transmission without moving parts,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:55.64,0:07:01.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,方法是使用相长干涉和相消干涉控制无线电波束的指向
Dialogue: 2,0:06:55.64,0:07:01.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,instead they use destructive and constructive interference to control the direction of the radio wave.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:01.89,0:07:06.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,每颗卫星的波束角为81度
Dialogue: 2,0:07:01.89,0:07:06.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Each satellite has a cone beam with a 81 degree range of view.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:06.08,0:07:13.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,550公里轨道的卫星可以覆盖宽500公里的地面范围
Dialogue: 2,0:07:06.08,0:07:13.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,With an orbit of 550 km each satellite can cover a circular area with a radius of 500 km.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:13.95,0:07:19.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,在太空叉原定轨道中 一颗卫星能覆盖1060公里宽
Dialogue: 2,0:07:13.95,0:07:19.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,At SpaceX's originally planned orbit this coverage had a radius of 1060 km.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:19.86,0:07:23.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,降低卫星轨道高度会减少覆盖范围 但也会减少时延
Dialogue: 2,0:07:19.86,0:07:23.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Lowering the altitude of a satellite decreases the area it can cover,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:23.77,0:07:25.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,降低卫星轨道高度会减少覆盖范围 但也会减少时延
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.77,0:07:25.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,but also decreases the latency.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:26.21,0:07:30.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个时延相比于传统的同步轨道通信卫星 降低的效果是非常显著的
Dialogue: 2,0:07:26.21,0:07:30.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is particularly noticeable for typical communications satellites
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.21,0:07:35.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个时延相比于传统的同步轨道通信卫星 降低的效果是非常显著的
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.21,0:07:35.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,operating in geostationary orbit at an altitude of about 36,000 kilometres.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.66,0:07:40.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,信号以光速往返地面与同步卫星需要240毫秒 是海底光缆的369%
Dialogue: 2,0:07:35.66,0:07:40.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,The time it takes data to travel up to the satellite and back down travelling at the speed of light
Dialogue: 1,0:07:40.81,0:07:47.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,信号以光速往返地面与同步卫星需要240毫秒 是海底光缆的369%
Dialogue: 2,0:07:40.81,0:07:47.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,is around 240 milliseconds 369% slower than our subsea cable.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:47.42,0:07:51.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,而Starlink选择了更低的轨道
Dialogue: 2,0:07:47.42,0:07:51.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, since Starlink is intending to operate at a much lower altitude,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:51.56,0:07:57.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,那么上下行的理论时延可以低至3.6毫秒
Dialogue: 2,0:07:51.56,0:07:57.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,the up and down link theoretical latency could be as low as 3.6 ms.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:57.00,0:08:03.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此 太空叉的星座需要的卫星数量相当巨大 才能做到全球覆盖
Dialogue: 2,0:07:57.00,0:08:03.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is why SpaceX needs so many satellites in their constellation in order to provide worldwide coverage.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:03.60,0:08:10.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,每颗Starlink卫星有四个相控阵列天线 位于图中的四个位置
Dialogue: 2,0:08:03.60,0:08:10.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,StarlinkEach individual Starlink satellite has four phased array antenna located here, here, here and here.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:10.38,0:08:15.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些指向性波束就是太空叉向FCC申请的主要内容
Dialogue: 2,0:08:10.38,0:08:15.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,This directional beam was an essential part of SpaceX's FCC approval application,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:15.65,0:08:19.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为上千颗卫星对地胡乱发送无线电波
Dialogue: 2,0:08:15.65,0:08:19.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,as thousands of satellites broadcasting undirected radio waves
Dialogue: 1,0:08:19.56,0:08:24.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,可能对其他通信方式产生严重干扰
Dialogue: 2,0:08:19.56,0:08:24.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,would cause significant amounts of interference with other communication methods.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:24.38,0:08:27.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,当一颗Starlink卫星接收到来自地面的数据
Dialogue: 2,0:08:24.38,0:08:27.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once that data is received by one Starlink satellite,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:27.62,0:08:31.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,那么它可以利用激光在卫星之间传输这个数据
Dialogue: 2,0:08:27.62,0:08:31.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,it can begin to transmit that information between satellites using lasers.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:31.90,0:08:33.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,数据每次在卫星中进行中转
Dialogue: 2,0:08:31.90,0:08:33.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,Each time we hop from satellites
Dialogue: 1,0:08:33.78,0:08:38.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,都会有一个光电转换的很小的延迟
Dialogue: 2,0:08:33.78,0:08:38.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,there will be a small delay as the laser light is converted to an electric signal and back again,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:38.51,0:08:40.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,不过延迟很小 可以忽略
Dialogue: 2,0:08:38.51,0:08:40.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it is too miniscule to consider.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:40.86,0:08:43.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,但到了激光这里 事情变得有意思起来了
Dialogue: 2,0:08:40.86,0:08:43.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,Things get tricky here with using lasers,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:43.25,0:08:48.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为我们需要让激光准确发射给相邻的接收卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:08:43.25,0:08:48.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,as we need to accurately hit the receiver on neighbouring satellites to transmit that data.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:48.42,0:08:52.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们先来看一下太空叉提交的星座内容
Dialogue: 2,0:08:48.42,0:08:52.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let's look at SpaceX's proposed constellation to see how this will work.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:52.61,0:08:59.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉第一阶段的1584颗卫星会占用24个轨道平面
Dialogue: 2,0:08:52.61,0:08:59.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX's first phase of 1584 satellites will occupy 24 orbital planes,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:59.84,0:09:04.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,每个轨道平面倾角53度 有66颗卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:08:59.84,0:09:04.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,with 66 satellites in each plane inclined at 53 degrees.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:04.28,0:09:05.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,看起来应该是这样
Dialogue: 2,0:09:04.28,0:09:05.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,That will look something like this.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:06.03,0:09:11.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,在同一轨道面的相邻卫星之间通信相对比较简单
Dialogue: 2,0:09:06.03,0:09:11.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Communication between neighbouring satellites in the same orbital plane is relatively simple,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:11.16,0:09:16.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为它们的前后相对位置是固定的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:11.16,0:09:16.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,as these satellites will remain in relatively stable positions in relation to each other.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:16.36,0:09:20.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,这可以提供我们该轨道面下一条线的通信
Dialogue: 2,0:09:16.36,0:09:20.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,This gives us a solid line of communication along a single orbital plane,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:20.80,0:09:26.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在很多情况下 一个轨道面是无法连接两个地点的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:20.80,0:09:26.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,but in many cases a single orbital plane will not connect two locations,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:26.27,0:09:30.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以我们要让不同轨道面的卫星也有通信能力
Dialogue: 2,0:09:26.27,0:09:30.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,so we need to be able transfer information between these planes too.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:30.81,0:09:36.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,这就需要精准定位 因为不同轨道面的卫星相对速度非常高
Dialogue: 2,0:09:30.81,0:09:36.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,This requires precise tracking, as the satellites travelling in neighbouring orbital planes
Dialogue: 1,0:09:36.11,0:09:40.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,这就需要精准定位 因为不同轨道面的卫星相对速度非常高
Dialogue: 2,0:09:36.11,0:09:40.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,are travelling incredibly quickly and will come in and out of view.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:40.17,0:09:44.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,这就需要Starlink卫星有随时切换到其他卫星的能力
Dialogue: 2,0:09:40.17,0:09:44.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,This means the Starlink satellite will need to switch to a new satellite in the network.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:44.96,0:09:48.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这是需要时间的 最好的例子是1分钟
Dialogue: 2,0:09:44.96,0:09:48.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,This can take time, the best figure I could find is about a minute
Dialogue: 1,0:09:48.76,0:09:52.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,来自于欧洲航天局数据中继卫星系统
Dialogue: 2,0:09:48.76,0:09:52.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,for the European Space Agency's Data Relay Satellite System,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:52.45,0:09:56.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,该系统是运营在同步轨道的网络星座
Dialogue: 2,0:09:52.45,0:09:56.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is a currently operating geostationary internet constellation
Dialogue: 1,0:09:56.24,0:10:01.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,设计用于服务欧洲的成像卫星和其他关键用途
Dialogue: 2,0:09:56.24,0:10:01.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,designed to serve European imaging satellites, and other time critical applications.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:01.05,0:10:06.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,比如偏远地区紧急服务一些部队 比如扑灭森林大火
Dialogue: 2,0:10:01.05,0:10:06.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,Such as serving emergency forces in remote areas, like those fighting forest fires.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:06.13,0:10:09.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,Starlink可能会更快 但也不可能是一瞬间做到
Dialogue: 2,0:10:06.13,0:10:09.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,Starlink may be faster, but it won't be instantaneous,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:09.34,0:10:12.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此 每颗卫星载有五个光学通信系统
Dialogue: 2,0:10:09.34,0:10:12.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,and thus it has 5 optical communication systems on board
Dialogue: 1,0:10:12.91,0:10:16.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,确保在任意时刻同时和四颗卫星保持通信
Dialogue: 2,0:10:12.91,0:10:16.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,to maintain a steady connection to 4 satellites at all times.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:16.98,0:10:21.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果我们使用Starlink在纽约和伦敦来回传输数据
Dialogue: 2,0:10:16.98,0:10:21.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,If we now use this system, transmitting from New York to London and back,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:21.33,0:10:26.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,最短的理论路径 使用真空光速作为传输速度
Dialogue: 2,0:10:21.33,0:10:26.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,with the shortest path possible, using the speed of light in a vacuum as our transfer speed,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:26.24,0:10:29.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,那么延迟可以低至43毫秒
Dialogue: 2,0:10:26.24,0:10:29.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can achieve a latency as low as 43 milliseconds.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:29.96,0:10:35.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,即使我们使用最短路径上的光纤 虽然这还不存在
Dialogue: 2,0:10:29.96,0:10:35.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even if we took the shortest route possible with an optic fibre, which does not exist,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:35.33,0:10:40.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,这这也要花55毫秒 慢28%
Dialogue: 2,0:10:35.33,0:10:40.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,this would take about 55 milliseconds, a 28% decrease in speed.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:40.08,0:10:46.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这个路程现实中的延迟是76毫秒 前面已经提到过
Dialogue: 2,0:10:40.08,0:10:46.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,The actual current return trip time for your average Joe is about 76 milliseconds, as we saw earlier.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:46.91,0:10:49.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,慢了77%
Dialogue: 2,0:10:46.91,0:10:49.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,A 77% decrease in speed.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:49.71,0:10:54.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,这对于位于两地的金融市场来说是一个极大的影响
Dialogue: 2,0:10:49.71,0:10:54.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is a huge deal for the two financial markets working out of these cities,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:54.24,0:10:57.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,几毫秒内可能就差出去上百万美元了
Dialogue: 2,0:10:54.24,0:10:57.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,with millions of dollars being moved in fractions of a second,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:57.61,0:11:02.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,更低的时延可以在价格波动中获得巨大优势
Dialogue: 2,0:10:57.61,0:11:02.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,having a lower latency would provide a massive advantage in capitalizing on price swings.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:02.80,0:11:06.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,实际上 这已经不是通信企业花如此大的价钱为这些特定业务提供服务了
Dialogue: 2,0:11:02.80,0:11:06.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, it wouldn't be the first time a communications company
Dialogue: 1,0:11:06.51,0:11:10.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,实际上 这已经不是通信企业花如此大的价钱为这些特定业务提供服务了
Dialogue: 2,0:11:06.51,0:11:10.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,has made a massive investment to specifically serve these groups.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:10.56,0:11:14.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,Hibernian快线是一个私营的海底光缆
Dialogue: 2,0:11:10.56,0:11:14.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Hibernian Express cable is a privately owned optic cable
Dialogue: 1,0:11:14.43,0:11:20.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,是目前位于新泽西Secaucus的NY4数据中心
Dialogue: 2,0:11:14.43,0:11:20.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,that is currently the lowest latency connection between the NY4 data centre in Secaucus, New Jersey
Dialogue: 1,0:11:20.54,0:11:26.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,到位于英国Slough的LD4数据中心延迟最低的线路 只有59.95毫秒
Dialogue: 2,0:11:20.54,0:11:26.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the LD4 data centre in Slough, England at just 59.95 ms,
Dialogue: 1,0:11:26.73,0:11:30.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,比Starlink理想值慢39.4%
Dialogue: 2,0:11:26.73,0:11:30.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,39.4% slower than our best time with Starlink.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:30.70,0:11:35.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,在它之前的最快纪录是AC-1光缆 延迟65毫秒
Dialogue: 2,0:11:30.70,0:11:35.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,The previous best time was held by the AC-1 cable at 65 ms.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:35.84,0:11:44.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了提升5毫秒的延迟 不惜花费3亿美元去修Hibernian快线
Dialogue: 2,0:11:35.84,0:11:44.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,At a cost of 300 million dollars this 5 ms increase in speed was justified to just connect across the Atlantic.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:44.37,0:11:51.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,你想想如果能再快17毫秒 那些敏感企业愿意花多少钱来买这个服务
Dialogue: 2,0:11:44.37,0:11:51.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,Imagine how much these time sensitive industries will be willing to pay for a 17-ms-increase in speed.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:51.64,0:11:56.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,而当我们发现这个延迟差距会随着传输距离增加而增加时 它的价值就更高了
Dialogue: 2,0:11:51.64,0:11:56.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,It becomes even more valuable when you realise this time differential increases
Dialogue: 1,0:11:56.40,0:11:58.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,而当我们发现这个延迟差距会随着传输距离增加而增加时 它的价值就更高了
Dialogue: 2,0:11:56.40,0:11:58.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,with increased transmission distance.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:58.65,0:12:01.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,纽约到伦敦距离还算近的
Dialogue: 2,0:11:58.65,0:12:01.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,New York to London is a relatively short distance.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:01.88,0:12:06.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,对于伦敦到新加坡的传输 提升就更明显了
Dialogue: 2,0:12:01.88,0:12:06.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,The improvements would be even more pronounced for a London to Singapore transmission,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:06.18,0:12:11.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,距离每提升一点 延迟降低的程度就更多
Dialogue: 2,0:12:06.18,0:12:11.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,for every additional kilometre we travel the potential gains in speed increase rapidly.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:11.41,0:12:16.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,但太空叉并不仅仅打算让Starlink的快速网络服务某些客户
Dialogue: 2,0:12:11.41,0:12:16.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,But SpaceX aren't just planning on serving this super fast internet to some customers,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:17.04,0:12:23.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们宣传该系统的宗旨是想让地球上每个人都能连接互联网
Dialogue: 2,0:12:17.04,0:12:23.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,they primarily advertise this system as a way to connect every human on this planet to the internet,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:23.08,0:12:26.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们也有很多空余的带宽服务这些人
Dialogue: 2,0:12:23.08,0:12:26.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they should have plenty of bandwidth left over to serve these people.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:26.69,0:12:31.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然互联网技术已经成为人类历史上发展最快的技术
Dialogue: 2,0:12:26.69,0:12:31.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although the internet has been one of the fastest growing technologies in human history,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:31.39,0:12:36.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,但到了2019年年末 全世界仍然有近40亿人没有“上线”
Dialogue: 2,0:12:31.39,0:12:36.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,by the end of 2019 more than half of the world's population will still be offline (4 billion).
Dialogue: 1,0:12:36.81,0:12:42.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,用户只需花大约200美元 使用Starlink的终端就能连接互联网
Dialogue: 2,0:12:36.81,0:12:42.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,Users will connect to this internet using a Starlink terminal which will cost around $200 each,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:42.51,0:12:47.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然这还是超出了很多第三世界国家人民的购买力
Dialogue: 2,0:12:42.51,0:12:47.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,this will still be far outside the purchasing power of many third world citizens,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:47.08,0:12:52.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这仅仅是开始 何况这已经比类似的产品便宜很多了
Dialogue: 2,0:12:47.08,0:12:52.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it's a start and vastly cheaper then similar currently available receivers
Dialogue: 1,0:12:52.03,0:12:55.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,比如Kymeta版本的锅盖就要三万美元
Dialogue: 2,0:12:52.03,0:12:55.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,like the Kymeta version at a price of $30,000.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:55.56,0:12:59.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,马一龙说这种锅盖足够平整 可以放在房顶或车顶
Dialogue: 2,0:12:55.56,0:12:59.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Elon Musk says that these will be flat enough to fit onto the roof of a car
Dialogue: 1,0:12:59.44,0:13:01.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,或者其他交通工具 比如船或飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:12:59.44,0:13:01.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,and other vehicles like ships and airplanes.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:01.98,0:13:05.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,这样 Starlink还可以与传统互联网服务商竞争
Dialogue: 2,0:13:01.98,0:13:05.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,This will allow Starlink to compete with traditional internet providers.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:05.81,0:13:10.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,据估计 美国从4G升级到5G
Dialogue: 2,0:13:05.81,0:13:10.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's estimated that moving the US from a 4G to a 5G wireless connection
Dialogue: 1,0:13:10.41,0:13:16.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,在未来七年内 要在光缆铺设上要花费1500亿美元
Dialogue: 2,0:13:10.41,0:13:16.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,will cost around $150 billion in fiber optic cabling alone over the next 7 years,
Dialogue: 1,0:13:16.45,0:13:21.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,而太空叉则要在100亿美元内完成整个Starlink项目
Dialogue: 2,0:13:16.45,0:13:21.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX plan to complete their entire Starlink project for as little as $10 billion.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:21.50,0:13:24.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,每颗Starlink卫星价值约30万美元
Dialogue: 2,0:13:21.50,0:13:24.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,Each Starlink satellite cost around $300,000
Dialogue: 1,0:13:24.18,0:13:27.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,对于通信卫星来说这已经是白菜批发价了
Dialogue: 2,0:13:24.18,0:13:27.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is already a massive cut in cost for communication satellites.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:27.85,0:13:33.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉还可以在发射费用上节省 因为他们有自家的猎鹰九号火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:13:27.85,0:13:33.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX are also saving on launch costs, as they are launching on their own Falcon 9 rocket,
Dialogue: 1,0:13:33.18,0:13:36.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,一般的卫星制造商可做不到
Dialogue: 2,0:13:33.18,0:13:36.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,something that no other satellite manufacturer has.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:36.59,0:13:44.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果进展顺利 在高级交易所支持下 Starlink预计每年可盈利300-500亿美元
Dialogue: 2,0:13:36.59,0:13:44.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,If everything goes to plan, Starlink is estimated to generate $30 billion to $50 billion in revenue each year
Dialogue: 1,0:13:44.00,0:13:47.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果进展顺利 在高级交易所支持下 Starlink预计每年可盈利300-500亿美元
Dialogue: 2,0:13:44.00,0:13:47.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,on the back of premium stock exchange memberships,
Dialogue: 1,0:13:47.10,0:13:50.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,碾压他们目前每年约30亿美元的利润
Dialogue: 2,0:13:47.10,0:13:50.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,demolishing their current annual revenue of around $3 billion.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:50.99,0:13:54.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这对于马一龙的长期目标是非常重要的
Dialogue: 2,0:13:50.99,0:13:54.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this is a vital part of Elon Musk's long term goals.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:55.05,0:14:00.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,Starlink赚来的钱可以让太空叉有比NASA还多的资金
Dialogue: 2,0:13:55.05,0:14:00.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,The money generated from Starlink will mean SpaceX will have vastly more funding than NASA.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:00.28,0:14:03.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,可以用于研发新火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:14:00.28,0:14:03.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Which could go on to fund research and development of new rockets
Dialogue: 1,0:14:03.98,0:14:08.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,研发未来向月球和火星殖民的技术
Dialogue: 2,0:14:03.98,0:14:08.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the technology needed to monetise lunar and martian colonies.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:08.52,0:14:12.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,目前来讲 Starlink的计划单纯是让世界更加联通
Dialogue: 2,0:14:08.52,0:14:12.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,For now the project is simply aiming to connect the world even more
Dialogue: 1,0:14:12.09,0:14:15.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,并为互联网不发达的第三世界国家的教育开辟新的道路
Dialogue: 2,0:14:12.09,0:14:15.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,and potentially open avenues for education for third world countries
Dialogue: 1,0:14:15.89,0:14:18.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,并为互联网不发达的第三世界国家的教育开辟新的道路
Dialogue: 2,0:14:15.89,0:14:18.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,that do not have adequate connections to the internet.
